1
00:00:44,677 --> 00:00:45,945
Do I have a lover?

2
00:00:46,246 --> 00:00:47,279
No, you don't.

3
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:50,016
You were just inspired, so you drew this.

4
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:54,687
What you said about Tao Sor remembering things, just how much does he remember?

5
00:00:54,988 --> 00:00:56,856
It's not a continuous memory,

6
00:00:58,158 --> 00:00:59,359
it's kind of like...

7
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:00,827
the suppressed memories...

8
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:02,929
are so deep,

9
00:01:03,596 --> 00:01:05,941
that not even the owner of the memories knows what they're looking for.

10
00:01:05,965 --> 00:01:08,525
Just letting your brother remember what happened the day before,

11
00:01:08,701 --> 00:01:09,702
how's that a bad thing?

12
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,130
That's because you don't know anything!

13
00:01:12,605 --> 00:01:14,140
What Tao Sor had to go through...

14
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:16,519
But I don't want Tao Sor to be in pain anymore.

15
00:01:16,543 --> 00:01:17,543
That's up to you!

16
00:01:18,044 --> 00:01:19,044
But I suggest...

17
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:23,917
sometimes not remembering at all is no different from running away?

18
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:25,718
I've proven to Tao Sor,

19
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:28,088
that I would be his memory for him!

20
00:01:28,321 --> 00:01:30,457
Chef Mochi, what are you doing?

21
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,091
I remember...

22
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,694
a client saying that we'll be making Moo Hong tomorrow?

23
00:01:35,295 --> 00:01:36,429
You remember that?

24
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,300
You must be confused, just wrap it up.

25
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:47,640
He's drawing these strange pictures, I have a bad feeling about this.

26
00:01:48,241 --> 00:01:49,542
It's nothing, Mom.

27
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:51,778
You don't have to be worried.

28
00:01:53,413 --> 00:01:54,881
I'll take care of everything.

29
00:02:05,725 --> 00:02:06,926
We came...

30
00:02:07,994 --> 00:02:08,994
here before?

31
00:02:09,395 --> 00:02:10,395
Yes.

32
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:12,799
You were so cared of the ocean then...

33
00:02:14,334 --> 00:02:15,668
so I took you here.

34
00:02:16,769 --> 00:02:17,871
We walked together,

35
00:02:21,841 --> 00:02:22,909
breathed together,

36
00:02:23,409 --> 00:02:24,409
and...

37
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,313
i happened to just... kiss you.

38
00:02:29,449 --> 00:02:30,817
Then you walked away,

39
00:02:31,618 --> 00:02:34,587
after that I found you here,

40
00:02:35,088 --> 00:02:37,724
and told you, that starting from that day,

41
00:02:38,391 --> 00:02:41,728
I would be the one to be your memory for you.

42
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:44,831
I don't...

43
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,134
remember anything.

44
00:02:52,739 --> 00:02:53,739
If so...

45
00:02:55,575 --> 00:02:57,844
let's create some new memories today.

46
00:06:25,551 --> 00:06:26,551
You know...

47
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:30,180
when I first found out that you could only have memories for one day,

48
00:06:30,857 --> 00:06:32,058
I couldn't believe it.

49
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:35,895
So I proved it by meeting you here everyday,

50
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:37,802
and changing my name each time.

51
00:06:39,499 --> 00:06:41,401
Really? And...

52
00:06:43,302 --> 00:06:44,404
which names did you use?

53
00:06:45,104 --> 00:06:46,639
My name is...

54
00:06:46,873 --> 00:06:50,243
Jackson, like Michael Jackson.

55
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:54,112
My name is Pop, like Soda Pop (Saja Boys Ref.)

56
00:06:54,113 --> 00:06:55,481
I'm Bruce, like...

57
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:58,351
Bruce Lee...

58
00:07:01,521 --> 00:07:02,521
Parker...

59
00:07:02,955 --> 00:07:06,058
The itsy bitsy spider, climbing down the spout.

60
00:07:06,626 --> 00:07:07,626
Don't make me tell you.

61
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:10,181
I don't know how I came up with those.

62
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,602
You probably took me for a joke, huh?

63
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:19,439
Not at all, you seemed...

64
00:07:20,039 --> 00:07:21,039
cute...

65
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,307
more than anything else.

66
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,013
There was one day...

67
00:07:29,682 --> 00:07:31,584
we watched the sunset here,

68
00:07:32,552 --> 00:07:33,552
it was so beautiful.

69
00:07:35,021 --> 00:07:36,381
I never forgot that day, you know?

70
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:42,428
I wanna remember too!

71
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:45,230
It's fine.

72
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:49,101
Just us being able to see the moon together...

73
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:52,305
is already very good.

74
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:09,822
I say we should get going.

75
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:12,592
You look tired.

76
00:08:16,095 --> 00:08:17,597
I don't wanna leave yet.

77
00:08:19,465 --> 00:08:20,666
Can we stay a bit longer?

78
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:22,735
But you really do look tired.

79
00:08:23,903 --> 00:08:24,904
I'm still okay!

80
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:27,746
I don't wanna go home just yet.

81
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:32,712
If I go back and fall asleep,

82
00:08:34,614 --> 00:08:35,982
when I wake up...

83
00:08:37,016 --> 00:08:39,218
I'll forget everything that happened today!

84
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,958
I wanna remember, Kim.

85
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:51,130
I want memories of my own.

86
00:09:06,412 --> 00:09:08,748
Do you still trust me?

87
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:14,352
In that case...

88
00:09:15,154 --> 00:09:17,356
I'm gonna take you to do something.

89
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:21,059
What are we going to do?

90
00:09:22,461 --> 00:09:23,461
Let's go first.

91
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,050
This...

92
00:09:45,851 --> 00:09:50,056
you're sure of right? That you're not going home tonight.

93
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:51,957
Yes!

94
00:09:59,198 --> 00:10:00,198
By the way,

95
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,168
why did we get this tattoo?

96
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,173
Blue whales...

97
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:10,543
are symbols of solitude.

98
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:12,477
But...

99
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:14,981
when 2 blue whales meet...

100
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:19,619
it's like meeting a certain person,

101
00:10:20,553 --> 00:10:23,889
where in a world so large, they can truly understand us.

102
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:25,658
It's so you'll know...

103
00:10:26,726 --> 00:10:28,894
that you'll always have me by your side.

104
00:10:31,731 --> 00:10:33,032
Have we ever did the thing?

105
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:39,137
Do...

106
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:41,273
you trust me?

107
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:47,580
Let's recall some memories and then...

108
00:10:48,447 --> 00:10:50,249
create some new ones.

109
00:11:05,364 --> 00:11:09,168
Ganbai!
(Others) Ganbai!

110
00:11:17,643 --> 00:11:19,879
We haven't hung out together like this in while!

111
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:21,146
Speaking of,

112
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:23,516
what occasion are we celebrating?

113
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:24,916
Huh?! (In Japanese)

114
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:27,285
Don't you remember?

115
00:11:27,653 --> 00:11:30,122
Today is the date that we all met!

116
00:11:32,558 --> 00:11:34,760
I was sent here all alone,

117
00:11:35,094 --> 00:11:36,529
I was still young back then!

118
00:11:37,463 --> 00:11:39,265
No friends, couldn't speak Thai...

119
00:11:42,401 --> 00:11:43,401
Of course we do!

120
00:11:43,602 --> 00:11:46,237
That day, me and Kluen thought you were gonna kill yourself,

121
00:11:46,238 --> 00:11:47,406
since you ran into the ocean.

122
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:50,008
Actually,

123
00:11:50,342 --> 00:11:53,412
I was just drinking beer and threw...

124
00:11:54,413 --> 00:11:55,413
the can away,

125
00:11:55,815 --> 00:11:58,384
And once I realized that it was wrong,

126
00:11:59,018 --> 00:11:59,418
I...

127
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:01,921
just went to go get the can back.

128
00:12:05,224 --> 00:12:06,358
In the blink of an eye,

129
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:09,695
we've been friends for almost 20 years.

130
00:12:10,596 --> 00:12:11,664
Yeah, that's right.

131
00:12:12,665 --> 00:12:14,066
Thank you guys so much,

132
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:15,968
for being my family,

133
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,838
and my friends.

134
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:20,772
Arigato na.

135
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:23,241
Right.

136
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:28,380
Drink, drink, drink, drink, drink!

137
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:35,421
Let's go!

138
00:12:36,288 --> 00:12:38,157
Eyy, let Kluen show some of his stuff!

139
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:41,359
You haven't played for a while!

140
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:44,363
I haven't played for a while!
- Yeah, just do it!

141
00:13:42,054 --> 00:13:45,724
This is after not playing for a while! That's awesome.

142
00:13:50,729 --> 00:13:52,131
Thank you guys so much,

143
00:13:52,932 --> 00:13:54,800
for being with me in times that are

144
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:58,838
happy, and also the hard times.

145
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:07,813
Having memories feels good like this, you know?

146
00:15:12,478 --> 00:15:13,779
Tao Sor!

147
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,936
Tao Sor!

148
00:16:16,175 --> 00:16:17,175
Where have you been?

149
00:16:20,112 --> 00:16:21,112
I couldn't sleep,

150
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:22,815
so I went out.

151
00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:25,184
You couldn't sleep the whole night?

152
00:16:26,251 --> 00:16:27,453
That means you...

153
00:16:28,354 --> 00:16:30,155
remember everything from last night?

154
00:16:30,956 --> 00:16:31,956
Yes.

155
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:33,791
Wait.

156
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:38,002
So where did you go last night?

157
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,435
Please excuse me to go draw.

158
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:46,538
Who'd you see? Kim?

159
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:51,743
Wait.

160
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,080
And what is this?

161
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:58,049
You got a tattoo?

162
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,387
Didn't I tell you to ask me before doing anything?

163
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:02,587
Talay.

164
00:17:04,056 --> 00:17:05,657
Can I just have my own life?

165
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,762
What's happening, kids?

166
00:17:14,199 --> 00:17:15,267
It's nothing, Mom.

167
00:17:16,602 --> 00:17:19,071
He's just a little stressed, I'll take care of it.

168
00:17:23,909 --> 00:17:24,909
Tao Sor,

169
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:27,880
the reason I have to know everything about you,

170
00:17:28,781 --> 00:17:32,418
is so I can tell you what happened the day before each time you wake up!

171
00:17:32,985 --> 00:17:35,354
And if I asked " Who is Kim"

172
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:37,990
how would you answer me?

173
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,894
Just the guy who took...

174
00:17:46,131 --> 00:17:48,600
He's just the guy who brought tourists to our resort.

175
00:17:49,134 --> 00:17:50,134
That's all!

176
00:17:55,507 --> 00:17:56,508
And what if...

177
00:17:57,342 --> 00:18:00,345
I said I dreamt of a boy drowning, and...

178
00:18:00,879 --> 00:18:02,081
someone saved the boy,

179
00:18:03,982 --> 00:18:05,702
what does that have anything to do with me?

180
00:18:05,984 --> 00:18:06,984
I think..

181
00:18:07,619 --> 00:18:09,021
You're too confused.

182
00:18:10,289 --> 00:18:13,292
I'll have Mor Kluen help figure out your condition.

183
00:18:15,394 --> 00:18:16,995
Don't bother, I'm perfectly fine.

184
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:20,499
I'm gonna recover my meories bit by bit,

185
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,333
please excuse me.

186
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:28,740
Talay,

187
00:18:28,841 --> 00:18:30,685
why is your brother dreaming of that all of a sudden?

188
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:32,311
Does he remember the past now, son?

189
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:37,916
Calm down, Mom. There's nothing going on, I'll take care of Tao Sor myself.

190
00:18:41,186 --> 00:18:43,555
I'm not gonna lost Tao Sor again for sure.

191
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:37,109
Have to go run some errands. I'll hurry back!

192
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:56,295
Shit!

193
00:19:56,562 --> 00:19:58,330
What happened last night?

194
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:02,868
Did Nao do something to me?

195
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:03,502
Or did...

196
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:04,903
I do something to Nao?

197
00:20:07,606 --> 00:20:08,806
That's probably not it, right?

198
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:18,416
No.

199
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,686
She's coming back in God knows when,

200
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,063
Oh, Siw!

201
00:20:32,464 --> 00:20:34,024
Why'd you leave without saying goodbye!

202
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,367
Or...

203
00:20:36,668 --> 00:20:38,670
what happened...

204
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,239
last night?

205
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,178
You won't even say goodbye?

206
00:20:46,845 --> 00:20:48,947
Why would I? I'm gonna be coming back.

207
00:20:49,481 --> 00:20:50,849
Are we ready to leave?

208
00:20:54,686 --> 00:20:56,054
Who's this?

209
00:20:56,655 --> 00:20:58,223
I'm here to pick up a client.

210
00:20:59,658 --> 00:21:01,693
I called a car to get to the airport.

211
00:21:03,562 --> 00:21:04,763
Why didn't you tell me?

212
00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:06,398
I could have driven you.

213
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:10,669
You were drunk last night, probably hungover. I didn't want to disturb you.

214
00:21:11,003 --> 00:21:14,006
Please disturb me, I want you to disturb me.

215
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:20,879
You can cancel the ride. As for the fee, I'll pay for it.

216
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:22,681
Thank you so much.

217
00:21:24,049 --> 00:21:26,585
Let's go. Don't forget your bag too.

218
00:21:34,693 --> 00:21:35,693
Dad!

219
00:21:35,861 --> 00:21:38,363
There's 2 ships that need maintenance.

220
00:21:38,897 --> 00:21:43,201
1 ship's fuel tank is leaking, I think we'll have to replace it.

221
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:46,505
As for the other one, the rust is starting to spread.

222
00:21:46,638 --> 00:21:50,609
Right now, I'm having the technician check what need to be replaced.

223
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,750
Let's use another ship for now,

224
00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:54,613
low season brings fewer clients.

225
00:21:56,415 --> 00:21:56,682
But...

226
00:21:57,249 --> 00:22:01,887
I think we should change them out now, so we can be ready for the high season.

227
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:04,423
Or should we do promotions?

228
00:22:04,589 --> 00:22:08,493
Like what Siw did last time, it could increase our profits, Dad.

229
00:22:09,494 --> 00:22:10,929
No, that's pointless.

230
00:22:11,463 --> 00:22:13,098
I'll go talk to some elders.

231
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:21,205
Dad?

232
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:23,308
What's happening? Dad?!

233
00:22:24,042 --> 00:22:25,043
What's wrong, Uncle?

234
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:26,812
Sang, should I call an ambulance?

235
00:22:26,878 --> 00:22:27,346
Don't!

236
00:22:27,546 --> 00:22:29,981
It'll take ages, I'll take him myself!

237
00:22:30,082 --> 00:22:32,883
Look after the house, okay? There's gonna be one last group of clients on their way.

238
00:22:32,884 --> 00:22:34,185
I'll leave it to you, Kim!

239
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:35,186
I'm counting on you!

240
00:22:40,559 --> 00:22:42,027
Yes!

241
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:47,599
We got so much today!

242
00:22:57,442 --> 00:22:58,442
Hey, Chef Mochi.

243
00:22:59,411 --> 00:23:00,879
You're not running today?

244
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:05,817
I can't run anymore today.

245
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,222
I planned to

246
00:23:11,656 --> 00:23:13,091
draw a lot more today.

247
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,660
And I'm afraid

248
00:23:15,927 --> 00:23:17,696
my memories of him will disappear.

249
00:23:18,897 --> 00:23:19,897
Wait..

250
00:23:20,699 --> 00:23:21,699
Chef Mochi..

251
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,100
What are you drawing?

252
00:23:23,935 --> 00:23:24,936
Where'd you see that?

253
00:23:25,604 --> 00:23:26,604
Oh...

254
00:23:26,838 --> 00:23:27,639
Me and...

255
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:30,175
Don't tell me, Kim...

256
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:41,520
Don't ever let Talay see this no matter what.

257
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:45,857
Daiji...

258
00:23:47,826 --> 00:23:49,227
Can you keep this picture for me?

259
00:23:51,363 --> 00:23:55,367
Ahh, no.
- Why not? You'd be helping me out.

260
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,802
No, no, no, no.

261
00:23:57,702 --> 00:23:59,237
You're the only one that can help me?

262
00:23:59,838 --> 00:24:05,210
Please? Daiji? Please help me!

263
00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:10,214
Daiji!

264
00:24:10,215 --> 00:24:12,484
Can you please help me?

265
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:15,787
Just a little? Please?

266
00:24:28,733 --> 00:24:30,969
Hi Kim! I'm waiting at the bridge now.

267
00:24:31,736 --> 00:24:32,736
Where are you?

268
00:24:32,904 --> 00:24:35,440
I don't think I can go see you.

269
00:24:37,242 --> 00:24:39,177
Something came up at home,

270
00:24:40,779 --> 00:24:42,814
I'll call you later tonight, okay?

271
00:24:43,248 --> 00:24:44,248
Oh..

272
00:24:45,784 --> 00:24:49,788
Okay. It's no problem, I'll just see you some other time.

273
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:03,768
What a shame!

274
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,538
I was gonna give him this picture.

275
00:25:10,809 --> 00:25:11,809
Daiji?

276
00:25:13,278 --> 00:25:14,279
Can you please keep...

277
00:25:16,781 --> 00:25:18,416
my memory for me?

278
00:25:36,968 --> 00:25:37,968
Let's go.

279
00:25:38,570 --> 00:25:39,570
We should get back.

280
00:25:53,685 --> 00:25:55,020
How are things at home?

281
00:25:56,288 --> 00:25:59,591
Uncle's back home, the doctor gave him some medication.

282
00:26:01,026 --> 00:26:04,029
They said that there's no symptoms to be worried about.

283
00:26:04,329 --> 00:26:05,564
No need to be stressed.

284
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:07,766
It's a relief that there's nothing big.

285
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:11,246
These days, my family's been experiencing a lot of stressful situations.

286
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:14,973
Our luck's been down, probably because of my quarter life crisis?

287
00:26:16,207 --> 00:26:18,710
That's got nothing to do with this, it's a matter of health.

288
00:26:20,445 --> 00:26:24,149
But I don't want you to experience any bad things like this, Tao Sor.

289
00:26:24,349 --> 00:26:25,349
I think...

290
00:26:26,017 --> 00:26:27,686
being able to meet you...

291
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,221
is one of the best things to happen to me.

292
00:26:37,329 --> 00:26:38,329
And...

293
00:26:38,697 --> 00:26:41,700
how would you know if you've ever experienced anything good before?

294
00:26:42,734 --> 00:26:43,734
Today...

295
00:26:44,135 --> 00:26:45,737
I drew so many pictues of us.

296
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,441
You know something?

297
00:26:50,942 --> 00:26:53,545
You're very talented in drawing.

298
00:26:57,882 --> 00:27:01,853
Some day, I'll take you to my studio.

299
00:27:02,253 --> 00:27:03,521
If I remember to.

300
00:27:04,422 --> 00:27:06,958
Deal! Because if you don't remember,

301
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:09,227
I'll go to your place myself!

302
00:27:13,598 --> 00:27:14,598
Tao Sor!

303
00:27:17,068 --> 00:27:18,068
Tao Sor!

304
00:27:20,939 --> 00:27:21,939
Yes?

305
00:27:23,608 --> 00:27:26,611
Nothing. I think you should get some rest.

306
00:27:35,887 --> 00:27:38,623
Kim. When I wake up,

307
00:27:39,624 --> 00:27:41,126
will I remember you?

308
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:44,896
I told you already, you don't have to worry about that.

309
00:27:45,463 --> 00:27:46,965
Even if you won't remember,

310
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:51,302
I'll be here, re-introducing myself each time.

311
00:27:53,104 --> 00:27:56,107
Trust me, okay? Get some rest.

312
00:28:08,119 --> 00:28:10,121
I love you, Kim.

313
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:22,833
And what is this?

314
00:28:23,435 --> 00:28:24,435
You got a tattoo?

315
00:28:25,804 --> 00:28:27,372
Can I just have my own life?

316
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,475
The reason I have to know everything about you,

317
00:28:31,009 --> 00:28:34,646
is so I can tell you what happened the day before each time you wake up!

318
00:28:36,314 --> 00:28:37,625
But did he choose to go with you?

319
00:28:37,649 --> 00:28:39,084
Or did you decide for him?

320
00:28:41,486 --> 00:28:42,787
Did he hurt me?

321
00:28:45,557 --> 00:28:47,392
He made your life chaotic.

322
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,096
You little...
- I love Tao Sor!

323
00:29:37,842 --> 00:29:41,079
You are Tao Sor, you love Kim.

324
00:29:41,513 --> 00:29:44,716
He is your boyfriend, don't tell anyone about this.

325
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:06,637
Tao Sor!

326
00:30:08,406 --> 00:30:09,808
Tao Sor! Why'd you lock your door?

327
00:30:13,278 --> 00:30:14,278
Tao Sor!

328
00:30:14,946 --> 00:30:15,946
Yes?

329
00:30:18,116 --> 00:30:19,117
Why'd you lock the door?

330
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:22,486
Oh...

331
00:30:23,321 --> 00:30:24,321
I don't know why.

332
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,929
I'm Talay, I'm your older brother.

333
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:32,964
Oh..

334
00:30:33,565 --> 00:30:34,565
Remember?

335
00:30:38,002 --> 00:30:39,103
I can't...

336
00:30:52,951 --> 00:30:56,788
Dad. Eat your food so you can take your medicine.
- Hm? Okay.

337
00:30:59,858 --> 00:31:02,778
Did you practice your breathing like the doctor told you to this morning?

338
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:06,831
I'm already breathing. If I wasn't, I'd be dead, right?

339
00:31:07,632 --> 00:31:11,169
I know, but I meant practicing breathing like the doctor prescribed.

340
00:31:11,336 --> 00:31:13,271
So you won't get stressed.

341
00:31:17,508 --> 00:31:18,977
We're having porridge today?

342
00:31:20,044 --> 00:31:22,513
In that case, I'll go eat something at the university.

343
00:31:22,647 --> 00:31:25,250
I woke up late. Finished work up a bit late.

344
00:31:26,384 --> 00:31:29,087
I'm off, Sang! See you, Dad.

345
00:31:35,693 --> 00:31:36,928
Everyone.

346
00:31:37,328 --> 00:31:39,464
Shall we get some cake today?

347
00:31:40,965 --> 00:31:41,965
Cake?

348
00:31:42,166 --> 00:31:44,669
You know, the chocolate cake from the regular spot.

349
00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:51,709
I won't have any, I'm cutting down on fat.

350
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:56,547
The doctor's making me watch my diet, some other time then.

351
00:32:35,853 --> 00:32:37,989
Hello, I'm picking up the cake I ordered.
- Hello.

352
00:32:38,189 --> 00:32:40,692
The name is Kim.
- Okay, please sit and wait for a moment.

353
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:50,401
The birthday cake for Tao Sor's ready!

354
00:32:57,442 --> 00:32:58,710
Thank you.

355
00:33:01,045 --> 00:33:02,045
Tao Sor!

356
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:09,320
It's your birthday?

357
00:33:11,155 --> 00:33:13,590
No. A client is having a birthday today,

358
00:33:13,591 --> 00:33:15,493
so I came to get the cake they ordered.

359
00:33:15,727 --> 00:33:17,962
By the way, do we know each other?

360
00:33:19,430 --> 00:33:20,765
We know each other very well.

361
00:33:21,366 --> 00:33:22,366
I'm Kim.

362
00:33:39,317 --> 00:33:41,652
I'm sorry. I have to get going.

363
00:33:42,086 --> 00:33:44,522
But I really wanna know...

364
00:33:46,124 --> 00:33:47,492
who you are.

365
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:50,528
Can we see each other again?

366
00:33:51,129 --> 00:33:52,129
Then...

367
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:55,033
we'll meet at the Siam Sea port.

368
00:33:55,867 --> 00:33:56,867
I'll be waiting.

369
00:33:58,236 --> 00:33:59,236
Can do.

370
00:34:06,778 --> 00:34:09,480
The birthday cake for Kim is ready!

371
00:34:37,675 --> 00:34:39,277
Happy Birthday, Kim!

372
00:34:43,247 --> 00:34:46,250
Actually, today's not really my birthday.

373
00:34:46,984 --> 00:34:48,753
Oh, then who's is it?

374
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:53,590
My older brother.

375
00:34:55,526 --> 00:34:56,526
Have a seat.

376
00:35:04,635 --> 00:35:06,003
And...

377
00:35:06,971 --> 00:35:08,606
your brother's not celebrating with you?

378
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,040
He's...

379
00:35:11,509 --> 00:35:12,844
not here anymore.

380
00:35:14,412 --> 00:35:16,280
We probably can't celebrate anymore.

381
00:35:18,683 --> 00:35:22,053
I just wanted to think about him today.

382
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:23,454
That's all.

383
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:25,523
If I heard that,

384
00:35:25,890 --> 00:35:27,191
as a brother, I'd be very happy.

385
00:35:27,625 --> 00:35:29,760
That someone remembers him.

386
00:35:30,328 --> 00:35:31,496
But me?

387
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:34,999
I can't even remember my own birthday.

388
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:39,169
How bout this?

389
00:35:39,370 --> 00:35:42,874
Why don't we celebrate your birthday, today.

390
00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:47,345
It'll just be us two, so we can take the boat out,

391
00:35:48,513 --> 00:35:49,881
and go somewhere we can be alone.

392
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:05,329
Don't be scared.

393
00:36:07,198 --> 00:36:08,966
I'll be right beside you.

394
00:36:14,405 --> 00:36:17,408
Happy Birthday,

395
00:36:17,608 --> 00:36:20,611
to you...

396
00:36:24,215 --> 00:36:25,215
So,

397
00:36:27,051 --> 00:36:28,586
let's make a wish together.

398
00:36:46,037 --> 00:36:49,040
You're... my boyfriend?

399
00:36:53,244 --> 00:36:54,244
Do...

400
00:36:55,112 --> 00:36:56,147
you remember me?

401
00:36:58,216 --> 00:36:59,717
Oh, that's not it.

402
00:37:00,117 --> 00:37:03,988
This morning I saw a note, and these drawings.

403
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:35,585
Do...

404
00:37:35,953 --> 00:37:37,588
you know the person in this drawing?

405
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:38,922
Oh...

406
00:37:39,457 --> 00:37:41,092
No, I don't. I just...

407
00:37:41,792 --> 00:37:44,795
dreamt that this boy saved another boy from drowning.

408
00:37:47,832 --> 00:37:50,835
So I just drew him.

409
00:37:58,809 --> 00:37:59,809
Are you okay?

410
00:38:00,478 --> 00:38:03,748
I think I'll tell the captain to go back.

411
00:38:05,249 --> 00:38:06,249
You wait here.

412
00:38:09,053 --> 00:38:10,254
Yes, that's right.

413
00:38:10,554 --> 00:38:12,356
This point, please fix it for me.

414
00:38:13,491 --> 00:38:14,825
Okay...

415
00:38:15,559 --> 00:38:17,428
Can do, send the file over to me too.

416
00:38:17,795 --> 00:38:18,795
Okay.

417
00:38:30,174 --> 00:38:31,174
Hey.

418
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:34,245
What are you doing here?

419
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:36,247
Where's my brother?

420
00:38:37,848 --> 00:38:38,949
How would I know that?

421
00:38:39,283 --> 00:38:41,152
Your brother took mine here, right?

422
00:38:43,287 --> 00:38:44,355
You mean Siw?

423
00:38:44,855 --> 00:38:45,890
No.

424
00:38:46,390 --> 00:38:48,959
Is there a problem? What did Kim do?

425
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,829
I just want to know where my brother is.

426
00:38:52,763 --> 00:38:53,998
My brother is sick.

427
00:38:54,165 --> 00:38:55,866
If anything happens to him,

428
00:38:56,267 --> 00:38:58,569
I won't be doing any more business with Siam Sea.

429
00:38:58,636 --> 00:39:00,204
Sang, go check.

430
00:39:00,771 --> 00:39:01,771
Okay, Dad.

431
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:25,029
It's true, Dad.

432
00:39:25,496 --> 00:39:26,736
There's one ship out right now.

433
00:39:26,997 --> 00:39:28,397
How are you taking care of things?!

434
00:39:28,532 --> 00:39:30,801
Well Dad, it's...

435
00:39:31,769 --> 00:39:33,604
it's the one with the issues.

436
00:39:34,672 --> 00:39:35,672
What did you say?

437
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:37,675
A faulty ship?

438
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:40,077
And you just let my brother go?!

439
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:44,048
I just found out as well, like you!

440
00:39:46,250 --> 00:39:47,451
Let's do this, Dad.

441
00:39:47,651 --> 00:39:49,463
I'll hurry and get some people to go look for them.

442
00:39:49,487 --> 00:39:49,954
Get to it!

443
00:39:50,254 --> 00:39:51,254
I'll go too!

444
00:41:27,284 --> 00:41:28,285
Are you okay?

445
00:41:28,986 --> 00:41:30,488
I'm okay, bro.

446
00:41:30,754 --> 00:41:32,857
You don't have to go, I'll take the clients myself.

447
00:41:34,291 --> 00:41:35,559
But this job...
- Just go home.

448
00:41:35,960 --> 00:41:36,960
It's okay.

449
00:41:37,428 --> 00:41:38,529
You've been tired all day.

450
00:41:38,996 --> 00:41:41,165
If I get any tips, I'll share them with you.

451
00:41:43,601 --> 00:41:46,237
Okay, bro. Thanks alot.

452
00:41:59,416 --> 00:42:00,918
Take care of yourself.

453
00:42:01,886 --> 00:42:03,954
Hurry back!

454
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:36,519
Tao Sor,

455
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:38,889
You can hear me, right?

456
00:42:41,325 --> 00:42:42,927
Forget everything.

457
00:42:44,194 --> 00:42:46,363
And come back to being my brother, okay?

458
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:48,265
If you really feel bad,

459
00:42:48,766 --> 00:42:50,000
then I beg you.

460
00:42:50,734 --> 00:42:53,304
Quit messing with that family's son!

461
00:42:53,537 --> 00:42:57,441
Any drawings that aren't my parents or me, get rid of all of them.

462
00:42:57,775 --> 00:43:00,210
Tao Sor has no need for these memories.

463
00:43:00,711 --> 00:43:03,380
We must clear out everything that would destroy his life.
